
JDBC Steps
	Download Jar -- DB Specific
	Load the drivers -- Driverclass name
	Create Connection -- url username password
				url		
					protocal
					dbname
					machine name/host/ip
					portno
					schema name
					
	Create Statement from connection
	Execute query using stmt
	get resultset
	close resources
	
	
	JDBC never supports DB independent feature
	Boilerplate code -- unncessary code other than business logic
	Developer must have SQL knowledge in depth
	Developer is responsible to map object fields to database coln
	EveryTime whenever your write a query
	At the time iterating resultset you need to map fields explicitly -- everytime
	JDBC doesnt supports -- oop -- inheritance --mapping(Associations) 
	JDBC doesnt supports Collection features
	JDBC doesnt supports caching mechanism
	JDBC -- Automatically tables will not be created -- you need to write create table query
	
	JDBC -- URL/Username/Password/Driverclass (dbspecific jars)
	
	Hibernate -- jdbc internally -- 
		JDBC -- URL/Username/Password/Driverclass (dbspecific jars)
			   dailect -- help 
			   
		
		objects.save() -- hql -- Mysql(Number)
							     Oracle(Num(10,0))
		int -- abc --
	
		
	
	hibernate-configuration - file  ---- hibernate.cfg.xml -- holds db info + mapping files
	hibernate -mapping -- file -- employee-mapping.xml -- ORM
	
		
	
